                            <comment id="14297675" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 21:09:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the only internal queries are either in tests or are on system tables, so this shouldn&apos;t be causing a problem.  Have you seen any problems from this, or are you just being proactive about it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14297748" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2015 21:46:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In any case, it&apos;s safe enough to commit, so +1, and committed as 05bbefd.  I did leave out the unit tests, because going directly through &lt;tt&gt;QueryProcess.executeInternal()&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t really test that the statement was invalidated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
